{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MFawaZjU2m6JcEgsVAbzsc","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All gates pass:\n- 149 test files, 3849 tests passing\n- 96.85% overall coverage (above 90% target)\n- All 157 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n---\n\n## Code Review Findings\n\n**Story:** 16-1-verification-tier-type-and-utilities.md\n\n**Issues Found:** 1 High, 2 Medium, 2 Low\n\n### HIGH Issues (fixed)\n\n1. **Parser tests had zero coverage of `tier` field** (verify-parser.test.ts) — `parseStoryACs` is tested extensively but no test ever asserted the `tier` property on returned `ParsedAC` objects. The tier derivation logic was entirely untested. **Fixed:** Added `tier` assertions to 5 existing tests and 3 new dedicated tier tests.\n\n### MEDIUM Issues (fixed)\n\n2. **`VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` rejected new tier values** (parser.ts L99) — The regex only matched `cli-verifiable|integration-required`. Story files using the new `<!-- verification: test-provable -->` syntax were silently ignored, falling back to heuristic classification. **Fixed:** Expanded regex to include all 4 new tier values.\n\n3. **`parseVerificationTag` return type excluded new tier values** (parser.ts L105) — Return type was `Verifiability | null`, making it impossible to return `VerificationTier` values. **Fixed:** Changed to `Verifiability | VerificationTier | null` and updated the `flushCurrent` logic to use new tier values directly when the tag is a `VerificationTier` value.\n\n### LOW Issues (not fixed)\n\n4. **`runtime-provable` tier unreachable via heuristic classification** — No keyword set maps to `runtime-provable` through the automatic classification path. Only explicit tags can assign it. This is by design for story 16-1 (story 16-2 addresses parser tier classification), but worth noting.\n\n5. **`VerificationStrategy` deprecation JSDoc exists but no migration path documented** — The `@deprecated` comment on `VerificationStrategy` says \"use `VerificationTier` instead\" but VerificationStrategy (docker/cli-direct/escalate) and VerificationTier (test-provable/runtime-provable/etc.) serve different conceptual purposes. The deprecation message may be misleading.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **Bugs found:**\n  - HIGH: Parser tests had zero tier field coverage — tier derivation logic was untested\n  - MEDIUM: `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` regex rejected new tier values — new `<!-- verification: test-provable -->` tags silently ignored\n  - MEDIUM: `parseVerificationTag` return type couldn't express new tier values, and tier derivation from new tags fell through to wrong default\n- **Code quality issues found but NOT fixed:**\n  - LOW: `runtime-provable` tier unreachable via heuristic classification (deferred to story 16-2)\n  - LOW: `VerificationStrategy` deprecation message misleading — it's not a 1:1 replacement for VerificationTier\n- **Coverage gaps:** None — all files above 80%, overall 96.85%\n- **Architecture concerns:** None — the bridge pattern via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` is sound for incremental migration\n- **Items sent back for re-development:** None\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 22\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 9, Edit: 7, Grep: 6, Glob: 2, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): `npx vitest run` full suite (~50 lines each, x2), `git diff --stat` (~12 lines)\n- Files read: 12 unique, 13 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0ee306c8cc929975 (use SendMessage with to: 'a0ee306c8cc929975' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 82438\ntool_uses: 44\nduration_ms: 386074</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7513e7c5-481d-406c-8e26-d0526a0df74d","uuid":"9eb1c490-0944-4017-8574-1f660db31d9b","timestamp":"2026-03-27T06:50:54.360Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-1-verification-tier-type-and-utiliti